20for%20donations.%20There%2C%20he%20also%20called%20the%20proceedings%20a%20%26quot%3BSHAM%20trial%26quot%3B%20and%20a%20form%20of%20%26quot%3BElection%20Interference.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDemocrats%20have%20forced%20me%20to%20stand%20trial%20in%20a%20frivolous%20lawsuit%20rather%20than%20be%20on%20the%20campaign%20trail%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20appears%20to%20want%20to%20keep%20the%20case%20political%2C%20rather%20than%20leave%20it%20to%20his%20lawyers%20to%20argue%20the%20legal%20merits%20of%20the%20attorney%20general's%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20entered%20the%20courtroom%20surrounded%20by%20not%20just%20his%20lawyers%2C%20but%20his%20political%20staff.%20His%20spokesperson%20Steven%20Cheung%20and%20advisor%20Jason%20Miller%20sat%20to%20the%20side%2C%20watching%20opening%20statements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20Trump's%20lawyers%2C%20Alina%20Habba%2C%20lambasted%20New%20York%20Attorney%20General%20Letitia%20James%2C%20an%20elected%20Democrat.%20In%20her%20opening%20statement%2C%20Habba%20said%20James%20could%20have%20brought%20the%20case%20years%20earlier%2C%20and%20that%20she%20ultimately%20brought%20the%20lawsuit%20for%20political%20reasons.%20James%2C%20she%20pointed%20out%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fletitia-james-trump-organization-investigation-record-2021-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eran%20for%20office%20partially%20on%20her%20record%20of%20going%20after%20the%20Trump%20family%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20attorney%20general's%20lawsuit%20alleges%20that%20Trump%2C%20Eric%20Trump%2C%20Donald%20Trump%20Jr.%2C%20and%20two%20other%20Trump%20Organization%20executives%20are%20liable%20for%20fraud%20for%20misrepresenting%20the%20values%20of%20the%20company's%20property%20in%20financial%20statements%20submitted%20to%20banks%20for%20loans.%20They're%20seeking%20to%20disgorge%20the%20company%20of%20its%20allegedly%20ill-gotten%20profits%2C%20ban%20the%20group%20from%20running%20a%20company%20in%20New%20York%20ever%20again%2C%20and%20have%20the%20judge%20issue%20%24250%20million%20in%20penalties.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-key-cases-civil-criminal-investigations-lawsuits-updates-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETrump%20has%20had%20a%20lot%20of%20court%20dates%20this%20year%3C%2Fa%3E.%20With%20four%20criminal%20cases%20and%20other%20civil%20litigation%20on%20the%20docket%2C%20he%20has%20many%20more%20coming%20up%2C%20giving%20him%20ample%20opportunities%20to%20use%20courthouses%20as%20rally%20sites%20while%20court%20officers%20handle%20the%20security.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225616%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22alina%20habba%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6419fc6950c7b20018f17bd5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223744%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAttorney%20Alina%20Habba%20is%20representing%20Trump%20in%20his%20New%20York%20fraud%20trial.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FBryan%20Woolston%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EKevin%20C.%20Wallace%2C%20a%20lawyer%20at%20the%20attorney%20general's%20office%2C%20showed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-trial-ag-shows-previously-unseen-deposition-that-showed-family-deny-fraud-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edeposition%20videos%20where%20Trump%20and%20his%20children%20shirked%20responsibility%20for%20those%20financial%20statements%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20said%20the%20videos%20demonstrated%20they%20were%20acting%20with%20intent%20to%20defraud%20banks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHabba%2C%20in%20response%2C%20said%20the%20snippets%20of%20video%20misrepresented%20her%20clients%20and%20were%20further%20evidence%20of%20the%20plaintiff's%20political%20motivations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20wasn't%20planning%20to%20speak%20today%20until%20I%20saw%20the%20attorney%20general%20speak%20outside%20and%20until%20Mr.%20Wallace's%20presentation%2C%26quot%3B%20Habba%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20her%20own%20statement%20on%20the%20courthouse%20steps%2C%20before%20the%20trial%20began%2C%20James%20said%20Trump%20should%20not%20be%20exempt%20from%20New%20York%20state's%20financial%20laws%20just%20because%20he%20was%20a%20former%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNo%20matter%20how%20rich%20or%20powerful%20you%20are%2C%20there%20are%20not%20two%20sets%20of%20laws%20for%20people%20in%20this%20country%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20rule%20of%20law%20must%20apply%20equally%20to%20everyone%2C%20and%20it%20is%20my%20responsibility%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20it%20does.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ETrump's%20campaign%20aides%20didn't%20return%20to%20court%20after%20lunch%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECheung%20and%20Miller%20sat%20on%20the%20side%20of%20the%20courtroom%20gallery%2C%20watching%20the%20fireworks.%20But%20at%20other%20times%2C%20they%20appeared%20bored%20and%20distracted.%20Engoron%20generally%20forbade%20cellphones%20from%20the%20room%2C%20and%20the%20two%20Trump%20campaign%20staffers%20appeared%20fidgety.%20Cheung%2C%20at%20some%20points%2C%20seemed%20to%20close%20his%20eyes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20far%20from%20the%20first%20time%20Trump%20and%20his%20attorneys%20have%20claimed%20that%20the%20cases%20against%20him%20are%20politically%20motivated.%20But%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjudges-slam-donald-trump-and-his-lawyers-for-political-litigation-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejudges%20have%20often%20found%20the%20opposite%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20That%20he%20has%20filed%20lawsuits%20for%20improperly%20political%20purposes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20year%2C%20a%20federal%20judge%20in%20Florida%20tossed%20one%20of%20Trump's%20lawsuits%20against%20the%20Democratic%20National%20Committee%2C%20Hillary%20Clinton%2C%20former%20FBI%20director%20James%20Comey%2C%20and%20a%20smattering%20of%20other%20people%20and%20entities%20that%20Trump%20harbors%20grudges%20against.%20The%20lawsuit%2C%20US%20District%20Judge%20Donald%20M.%20Middlebrooks%2C%20wrote%2C%20was%20part%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Bpattern%20of%20misusing%20the%20courts%20to%20serve%20political%20purposes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20case%20should%20never%20have%20been%20brought%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BIts%20inadequacy%20as%20a%20legal%20claim%20was%20evident%20from%20the%20start.%20No%20reasonable%20lawyer%20would%20have%20filed%20it.%20Intended%20for%20a%20political%20purpose%2C%20none%20of%20the%20counts%20of%20the%20amended%20complaint%20stated%20a%20cognizable%20legal%20claim.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Letitia%20James%20Trump%20civil%20trial%20court%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651b1a82617692f0d03ce1bb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221666%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENew%20York%20attorney%20general%20Letitia%20James%20steps%20out%20of%20the%20courtroom%20doing%20a%20short%20break%20in%20the%20civil%20business%20fraud%20trial%20against%20former%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20at%20New%20York%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20Monday%2C%20Oct.%202%2C%202023%2C%20in%20New%20York.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FSeth%20Wenig%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMiddlebrooks%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-lawyers-sanctioned-by-courts-election-lawsuits-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esanctioned%20Trump%20and%20his%20lawyers%20in%20that%20case%3C%2Fa%3E.%20When%20they%20asked%20him%20to%20reconsider%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FJayShams%2Fstatus%2F1703795105713246711%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehe%20refused%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Middlebrooks%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FJayShams%2Fstatus%2F1703795613287010717%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%20in%20a%20ruling%20last%20month%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Trump%20has%20continued%20to%20try%20to%20use%20the%20courts%20for