EScientists%20say%20this%20hybrid%2C%20also%20known%20as%20a%20dogxim%2C%20is%20a%20sign%20of%20a%20growing%20problem.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EContact%20between%20wildlife%20and%20humans'%20domestic%20animals%20may%20increase%20the%20risk%20of%20disease%20transmission.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ENext%20time%20you%20see%20a%20fox%20when%20out%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-become-a-professional-dog-walker-what-its-like-2023-2%5C%22%3Ewalking%20with%20your%20dog%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20pause%20for%20a%20moment%20and%20ponder%20their%20relatedness.%20Dogs%20and%20foxes%20are%20distinct%20but%20distantly%20related%20canine%20species.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUntil%20recently%2C%20scientists%20thought%20it%20was%20impossible%20for%20them%20to%20breed.%20However%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdog-fox-hybrid-discovered-brazil-hit-by-car-2023-9%5C%22%3Ediscovery%20of%20a%20dog-fox%20hybrid%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Brazil%20suggests%20that%20%26quot%3BThe%20Fox%20and%20the%20Hound%26quot%3B%20might%20sometimes%20be%20a%20little%20more%20%26quot%3BLady%20and%20the%20Tramp.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20recent%20identification%20of%20the%20dog-fox%20hybrid%20known%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bdogxim%26quot%3B%20(a%20cross%20between%20dog%20and%20graxaim-do-campo%2C%20the%20Portuguese%20name%20for%20pampas%20fox)%20in%20Brazil%20also%20raises%20concerns%20about%20the%20impact%20that%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdogs-disrupt-wildlife-too-2013-2%5C%22%3Epet%20dogs%20might%20have%20on%C2%A0wild%20animal%3C%2Fa%3E%20populations%20and%20their%20survival.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20female%2C%20dog-like%20creature%20was%20first%20noticed%20when%20she%20was%20hit%20by%20a%20car%20and%20taken%20to%20a%20wildlife%20rehabilitation%20facility.%20The%20staff%20at%20the%20wildlife%20centre%20noticed%20she%20had%20a%20strange%20mix%20of%20physical%20and%20behavioural%20characteristics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20pricked%20ears%20and%20preference%20for%20eating%20small%20mammals%20seemed%20fox-like%2C%20but%20her%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-little-dogs-bark-more-than-big-dogs-2017-8%5C%22%3Ebarking%20was%20more%20reminiscent%20of%20a%20dog%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Throughout%20the%20centuries%20there%20have%20been%20unverified%20reports%20of%20fox-dog%20hybrids%2C%20but%20none%20have%20been%20confirmed%20before%20with%20genetic%20testing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGenetic%20testing%20revealed%20that%20she%20was%20a%20hybrid%20between%20a%20female%20pampas%20fox%20(Lycalopex%20gymnocercus)%20and%20a%20male%20domestic%20dog%20(Canis%20lupus%20familiaris).%20This%20is%20the%20first%20documented%20case%20of%20a%20dog-fox%20hybrid.%20Genetic%20analysis%20revealed%20she%20had%20a%20total%20of%2076%20chromosomes%2C%20compared%20to%20the%2078%20chromosomes%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fice-age-wolf-dna-suggests-dogs-were-domesticated-in-asia-2022-6%5C%22%3Edomestic%20dog%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%2074%20of%20the%20pampas%20fox.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20is%20a%20hybrid%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpizzly-bears-polar-grizzly-hybrid-spread-due-to-climate-crisis-2021-4%5C%22%3EHybridization%20is%20when%C2%A0two%20species%20mate%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20produce%20offspring%20with%20mixed%20genetic%20ancestry.%20Normally%2C%20animals%20only%20mate%20with%20members%20of%20their%20own%20species.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDifferences%20in%20the%20number%20of%20chromosomes%20(the%20structure%20in%20which%20DNA%20is%20packaged%20within%20the%20cell%20nucleus)%20often%20make%20species%20genetically%20incompatible%20with%20each%20other.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frare-video-seal-inflates-nose-like-ballon-in-mating-ritual-2022-9%5C%22%3EMating%20behaviour%20and%20courtship%20rituals%3C%2Fa%3E%20tend%20to%20be%20individual%20to%20a%20species%2C%20such%20as%20the%20vocalizations%20of%20rutting%20deer%2C%20as%20is%20reproductive%20anatomy%20and%20physiology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22youtube%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%20%3Ciframe%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FKTCw5VkexbY%3Fsi%3DebiUiGQDAHKR8BHY%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20well-known%20hybrids%2C%20such%20as%20mules%20(horse%20and%20donkey)%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frare-liliger-born-2012-9%5C%22%3Eligers%3C%2Fa%3E%20(male%20lion%20and%20female%20tiger)%20and%20tigons%20(male%20tiger%20and%20female%20lion)%2C%20are%20a%20result%20of%20human%20intervention.%20A%20lion%20and%20tiger%20would%20never%20meet%20naturally%20in%20the%20wild%2C%20as%20their%20native%20ranges%20are%20too%20far%20apart.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20more%20closely%20related%20(and%20thus%20genetically%20alike)%20two%20species%20are%2C%20the%20higher%20the%20chance%20of%20successful%20hybridization.%20For%20example%2C%C2%A0dogs%20(Canis%20lupus%20familiaris)%20and%20grey%20wolves%20(Canis%20lupus)%C2%A0only%20diverged%20between%2011%2C000%20and%2035%2C000%20years%20ago.%C2%A0Wolf-dog%20hybrids%C2%A0are%C2%A0relatively%20common%C2%A0because%20their%20genetics%2C%20reproductive%20anatomy%20and%20behaviour%20are%20still%20fairly%20similar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpizzly-bear-and-other-hybrid-animals-2014-8%5C%22%3EMost%20hybrids%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20sterile%2C%20meaning%20they%20are%20biological%20dead-ends.%20Even%20if%20differences%20in%20chromosome%20numbers%20and%20behaviour%20don't%20prevent%20two%20species%20from%20producing%20young%2C%20it%20may%20make%20the%20hybrid%20infertile.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHow%20common%20are%20hybrids%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHybrids%20are%20more%20widespread%20than%20you%20might%20think%20%E2%80%94%20they%20are%20all%20around%20us%20in%20the%20plant%20world%2C%20both%20natural%20and%20as%20a%20result%20of%20human%20intervention.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearch%20suggests%20that%20approximately%C2%A025%25%20of%20plant%20and%2010%25%20of%20animal%20species%C2%A0have%20been%20affected%20by%20interbreeding%20in%20the%20wild.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20domesticated%20species%20can%20breed%20with%20their%C2%A0wild%20relatives%C2%A0too.%20In%20Poland%2C%20a%202018%20study%20found%20high%20numbers%20of%20free-living%20wild%20boars%20had%20domestic%20genes%2C%20for%20example.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHybrid%20offspring%20are%20not%20always%20infertile%2C%20and%20some%20people%20are%20concerned%20about%20how%20this%20affects%20the%20long-term%20survival%20and%20purity%20of%20individual%20species.%20Hybrids%C2%A0can%20out-compete%20and%20eventually%20even%20replace%C2%A0their%20parent%20species.%20For%20endangered%20species%20with%20small%2C%20fragile%20populations%2C%20this%20is%20a%20serious%20threat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20case%20of%20the%20dogxim%2C%20her%20fertility%20was%20not%20verified.%20Sadly%2C%C2%A0reports%20suggest%20she%20has%20since%20died%2C%20so%20we%20will%20probably%20never%20know.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhy%20are%20hybrids%20controversial%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHybridization%20is%20important%20in%20the%20evolution%20of%20species%2C%20allowing%20populations%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanimals-adapting-to-urbanization-climate-change-2018-12%5C%22%3Eadapt%20to%20changing%20environments%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Early%20humans%20are%20widely%20recognised%20in%20science%20to%20have%20mated%20with%20Neanderthals%2C%20helping%20our%20ancestors%20survive%20in%20some%20harsh%20environments.%20Long%20term%2C%20hybrids%20can%20lead%20to%20the%20development%20of%20entirely%20new%20species.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20are%20also%20negative%20consequences.%C2%A0Physical%20abnormalities%20are%20common%20in%20hybrids%C2%A0including%20changes%20to%20skull%2C%20dental%20and%20horn%20structures%2C%C2%A0as%20seen%20in%20hybrid%20wildebeest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHybridization%20is%20also%20a%20problem%20for%20vulnerable%20populations%20or%20endangered%20species%2C%20leading%20to%20reduced%20fitness%20and%20therefore%20the%20survival%20of%20individuals%20and%20even%20whole%20populations.%20The%20Scottish%20wildcat%20wild%20population%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20is%20now%20almost%20entirely%20made%20up%20of%20wildcat-domestic%20cat%20hybrids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20does%20the%20dog-fox%20hybrid%20tell%20us%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20dog-pampas%20fox%20hybrid%20strongly%20suggests%20that%20contact%20between%20wild%20and%20domestic%20species%20is%20increasing%2C%20possibly%20because%20of%C2%A0human%20settlements%20encroaching%C2%A0on%20wild%20habitats.%20This%20can%20also%C2%A0significantly%20increase%20disease%20transmission%20risks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20dogxim%20might%20well%20be%20a%20warning%20of%20the%20destructive%20impact%20humans%20and%20domesticated%20animals%20are%20having%20on%20biodiversity.%20We%20don't%20know%20how%20many%20other%20hybrids%20may%20be%20living%20in%20the%20wild.%20Although%20the%20pampas%20fox%20is%20not%20considered%20endangered%2C%20this%20example%20of%20hybridization%20between%20a%20domestic%20and%20wild%20species%20signals%20the%20importance%20of%20monitoring%20interactions%20between%20different%20species%2C%20to%20protect%20vulnerable%20or%20numerically%20low%20populations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20important%20to%20note%20that%20the%20pampas%20fox%20species%20is%20very%20different%20to%20the%C2%A0red%20fox%20(Vulpes%20vulpes).%20We%20probably%20do%20not%20need%20to%20worry%20about%20creating%20dog-fox%20hybrids%20on%20our%20daily%20dog%20walks%2C%20because%20of%20the%20genetic%20distance%20between%20the%20two.%20However%2C%20the%20dogxim%20should%20warn%20us%20that%20our%20dogs'%20interactions%20with%20nature%20can%20have%20unexpected%20consequences.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22author%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fprofiles%2Fjacquelin