2cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22What%20Are%20mRNA%20Vaccines%20That%20Earned%20Two%20Scientists%20Nobel%20Prize%20In%20Medicine%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20coronavirus%20pandemic%20brought%20global%20renown%20to%20the%20mRNA%20technology%20that%20underpins%20vaccines%20from%20Pfizer%2FBioNTech%20and%20Moderna%2C%20and%20on%20Monday%20earned%20a%20Nobel%20Prize%20for%20two%20scientists%20who%20have%20been%20key%20to%20its%20development.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EKatalin%20Kariko%20of%20Hungary%20and%20Drew%20Weissman%20of%20the%20United%20States%20won%20the%20Nobel%20Medicine%20Prize%20for%20their%20work%20on%20%26quot%3Bnucleoside%20base%20modifications%20that%20enabled%20the%20development%20of%20effective%20mRNA%20vaccines%20against%20COVID-19%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThese%20types%20of%20jabs%20are%20new%20but%20researchers%20have%20been%20working%20for%20decades%20to%20try%20to%20figure%20out%20how%20to%20use%20messenger%20RNA%20(ribonucleic%20acid)%20for%20other%20vaccinations%20and%20to%20treat%20illnesses%20from%20AIDS%20to%20cancer.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%3EHow%20does%20it%20work%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EMessenger%20RNA's%20job%20in%20the%20body%20is%20to%20help%20deliver%20specific%20instructions%20from%20DNA%20to%20cells.%20In%20the%20case%20of%20the%20Pfizer%2FBioNTech%20and%20Moderna%20jabs%2C%20lab-generated%20mRNA%20tells%20human%20cells%20to%20create%20antigens%20--%20proteins%20that%20are%20similar%20to%20ones%20found%20in%20the%20Covid-19%20virus.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThanks%20to%20those%20antigens%2C%20a%20person's%20immune%20system%20learns%20how%20to%20fight%20the%20virus%20and%20neutralise%20Covid%20if%20it%20enters%20the%20body.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20cells%20create%20these%20proteins%2C%C2%A0the%20body%20breaks%20down%20the%20mRNA%20instructions%20and%20gets%20rid%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESuch%20direct%20communication%20with%20cells%20is%20revolutionary%20--%20classic%20vaccines%20aimed%20to%20provoke%20an%20immune%20response%20by%20injecting%20a%20neutralised%20form%20of%20a%20virus%20or%20antigens%20into%20the%20system.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%3EWhere%20did%20this%20come%20from%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20big%20breakthrough%2C%20in%20the%20late%201970s%2C%20was%20in%20using%20mRNA%20to%20make%20test-tube%20cells%20produce%20proteins.%20A%20decade%20later%2C%20scientists%20were%20able%20to%20get%20the%20same%20results%20in%20mice%2C%20but%20mRNA%20still%20had%20two%20major%20drawbacks%20as%20a%20medical%20tool.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFor%20one%20thing%2C%20cells%20in%20live%20animals%20resisted%20synthetic%20mRNA%2C%20provoking%20a%20dangerous%20immune%20response.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20top%20of%20that%2C%20mRNA%20molecules%20are%20fragile%2C%20making%20them%20difficult%20to%20deliver%20to%20the%20system%20without%20altering%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%202005%2C%20Kariko%20and%20Weissman%20of%20Penn%20State%20University%20published%20a%20groundbreaking%20study%20showing%20that%20a%20lipid%20--%20or%20fat%20molecule%20--%20envelope%20could%20safely%20deliver%20mRNA%20without%20negative%20effects.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20research%20caused%20a%20buzz%20in%20the%20pharmaceutical%20community%20and%20start-ups%20dedicated%20to%20mRNA%20therapies%20began%20to%20pop%20up%20around%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%3EWhat%20else%20can%20mRNA%20do%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EScientists%20have%20worked%20on%20developing%20mRNA%20jabs%20for%20illnesses%20like%20seasonal%20flu%2C%20rabies%20and%20Zika%2C%20as%20well%20as%20those%20that%20have%20remained%20vaccine-resistant%20until%20now%2C%20including%20malaria%20and%20AIDS.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EResearchers%20have%20also%20started%20testing%20personalised%20treatments%20on%20cancer%20patients%2C%20using%20samples%20of%20the%20proteins%20in%20their%20tumours%20to%20create%20specialised%20mRNA.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20then%20triggers%20the%20immune%20system%20to%20target%20specific%20cancer%20cells.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20mRNA%20platform%20is%20versatile%2C%26quot%3B%20University%20of%20Pennsylvania%20biochemist%20Norbert%20Pardi%20told%20AFP.%20%26quot%3BAny%20protein%20can%20be%20encoded%20as%20mRNA%20so%20there%20are%20many%20potential%20applications.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696269540000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-10%2Fur769ifg_katalin-kariko-drew-weissman-nobel-prize-twitter-650-_650x400_02_October_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwhat-are-mrna-vaccines-that-earned-two-scientists-nobel-prize-in-medicine-4443885%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22This%20year's%20Nobel%20Prize%20in%20Medicine%20has%20been%20awarded%20to%20scientists%20for%20discoveries%20that%20enabled%20the%20development%20of%20mRNA%20vaccines%20against%20COVID-19.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwhat-are-mrna-vaccines-that-earned-two-scientists-nobel-prize-in-medicine-4443885%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwhat-are-mrna-vaccines-that-earned-two-scientists-nobel-prize-in-medicine-4443885%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwhat-are-mrna-vaccines-that-earned-two-scientists-nobel-prize-in-medicine-4443885%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Double%20rainbow%20and%20lightning%20strikes%20caught%20on%20camera%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696269470000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F106F9%2Fproduction%2F_131312376_p0gj0hzc.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-us-canada-66987626%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%2