Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWith%20minor%20edits%20for%20style%2C%20this%20is%20the%20full%20text%20of%20their%20conversation.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%C2%A0Hello%2C%20and%20welcome%20to%20a%20special%20interview%20for%20%3Ci%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fi%3E.%20A%20recently%20published%20book%20argues%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20constitution%20is%20colonial.%20It%E2%80%99s%20called%20%3Ci%3EThe%20Colonial%20Constitution%3C%2Fi%3E%2C%20and%20it%20raises%20a%20fundamental%20question%3A%20is%20the%20book%20right%20and%20is%20our%20constitution%20really%20colonial%2C%20or%20is%20that%20a%20mistaken%20view%3F%20Joining%20me%20now%20to%20answer%20that%20question%20is%20the%20author%20himself%2C%20the%20research%20director%20of%20the%20Vidhi%20Center%20for%20Legal%20Policy%2C%20Arghya%20Sengupta.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EArghya%20Sengupta%2C%20I%20want%20to%20focus%20this%20interview%20on%20your%20belief%20that%20the%20Indian%20constitution%20is%20colonial%2C%20and%20if%20I%E2%80%99ve%20understood%20your%20book%20correctly%20you%20have%20two%20broad%20arguments%20for%20saying%20so.%20Let%E2%80%99s%20go%20through%20them%20one%20by%20one.%20To%20begin%20with%2C%20you%20write%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20constitution%20of%20India%20is%20a%20colonial%20document.%20It%E2%80%99s%20colonial%20for%20the%20simple%20factual%20reason%20that%20it%20is%20heavily%20borrowed%20from%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20Act%201935%2C%20a%20fact%20that%20has%20been%20widely%20glossed%20over%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20true%2C%20but%20only%20in%20the%20sense%20that%20that%E2%80%99s%20the%20broad%20outline%20structure%2C%20and%20you%20can%20see%20that%20when%20you%20go%20on%20in%20your%20book%20to%20say%20%E2%80%9CFundamental%20rights%20were%20guaranteed%20to%20every%20citizen%20of%20independent%20India%20in%20a%20marked%20departure%20from%20colonial%20rule%E2%80%9D.%20So%20is%20there%20a%20contradiction%20inherent%20here%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20It%20needn%E2%80%99t%20have%20been%20based%20on%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20Act%20of%201935.%20When%20the%20constitution%20framers%20started%20their%20task%20in%201946%20on%20the%209th%20of%20December%2C%20the%20question%20that%20they%20asked%20could%20have%20been%20%E2%80%98What%20kind%20of%20India%20do%20we%20envisage%3F%E2%80%99%20It%20could%20have%20been%2C%20%E2%80%98What%20is%20the%20constitutional%20structure%20that%20gets%20us%20to%20that%20India%E2%80%99%2C%20but%20rather%20the%20questions%20that%20were%20asked%20were%3A%20%E2%80%98How%20can%20we%20adapt%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20Act%20to%20make%20it%20suitable%20for%20independent%20India%3F%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98What%20do%20we%20need%20to%20change%2C%20what%20do%20we%20need%20to%20incorporate%3F%E2%80%99%20The%20fact%20is%2C%20that%20they%20didn%E2%80%99t%20start%20off%20with%20a%20clean%20slate.%20What%20they%20chose%2C%20as%20what%20was%20written%20on%20the%20slate%20before%20they%20started%2C%20was%20factually%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20Act.%20That%20may%20not%20be%20a%20bad%20thing%20entirely%2C%20because%20they%20were%20in%20a%20hurry%20and%20they%20needed%20to%20have%20something%20to%20begin%20with%3B%20but%20it%20is%20a%20fact%20and%20that%20fact%20has%20been%20lost.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FgtXTk8Zs-ns%3Ffeature%3Doembed%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Does%20India%20Have%20a%20Colonial%20Consitituion%20Or%20is%20That%20a%20Mistaken%20View%3F%20%7C%20Karan%20Thapar%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22473%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20Let%E2%80%99s%20pick%20up%20on%20the%20point%20you%20make%2C%20that%20it%20needn%E2%80%99t%20have%20been%20based%20on%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20Act.%20In%20fact%2C%20in%20your%20book%20you%20say%2C%20%E2%80%9CBorrowing%20from%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20Act%20was%20a%20missed%20opportunity%E2%80%9D.%20You%20then%20say%2C%20%E2%80%9CAmbedkar%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20drafting%20committee%20members%20did%20not%20consider%20forms%20of%20local%20government%20and%20constitutional%20thinking%20in%20ancient%20and%20medieval%20India%E2%80%9D.%20But%20surely%2C%20India%20is%20far%20too%20big%20a%20country%20to%20have%20been%20ruled%20by%20village%20panchayats.%20Leave%20aside%20second%20and%20third%20century%20BC%20Buddhist%20sanghas%20and%20shakyas.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3C%2Fb%3E%3A%20Absolutely.%20I%20think%20that%20there%E2%80%99s%20one%20fallacy%20that%20we%20always%20tend%20to%20make%20when%20we%20think%20about%20going%20beyond%20colonial%20rule%2C%20which%20is%20that%20we%20tend%20to%20go%20back%202%2C000%20years.%20You%E2%80%99re%20absolutely%20right%2C%20that%20we%20cannot%20go%20back%20to%20a%20pre-modern%20state.%20It%20cannot%20be%20anyone%E2%80%99s%20argument%20that%20we%20go%20back%20to%20a%20state%20that%20essentially%20is%20not%20modern.%20But%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20there%20has%20been%20a%20lot%20of%2C%20if%20I%20may%20use%20the%20term%2C%20constitutional%20activity%20in%20India%20right%20from%20the%20Buddhist%20shakyas%20that%20you%20spoke%20about.%20Even%20before%20that%2C%20right%20down%20through%20the%20Cholas%20in%20the%20South%2C%20where%20a%20lot%20of%20very%20interesting%20stuff%20went%20on%2C%20through%20the%20time%20of%20the%20Mughals.%20As%20many%20people%20have%20written%20about%20the%20medieval%20period%2C%20India%20has%20always%20been%20a%20contest%20between%20empires%20and%20kingdoms%2C%20and%20you%20see%20how%20division%20of%20powers%20have%20been%20worked%20out%20in%20a%20very%20interesting%20way.%20There%E2%80%99s%20a%20lot%20of%20material%20there.%20But%20what%20happens%20is%2C%20and%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20blame%20the%20constitutional%20framers%20as%20I%E2%80%99ve%20said%2C%20is%20that%20the%20exigencies%20of%20time%20and%20the%20urgency%20of%20having%20a%20new%20constitution%20come%20out%20quickly%20means%20that%20they%20don%E2%80%99t%20go%20into%20that%20exercise%20at%20all%2C%20and%20they%20take%20what%20is%20closest%20at%20hand.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20Let%20me%20once%20again%20quote%20from%20your%20book.%20You%20say%2C%20%E2%80%9CVesting%20sovereign%20power%20at%20the%20local%20level%2C%20which%20clearly%20our%20constitution%20did%20not%20do%2C%20would%20enable%20individuals%20to%20directly%20participate%20in%20government%E2%80%9D.%20There%E2%80%99s%20a%20great%20danger%20that%20if%20that%20had%20happened%2C%20you%20would%20have%20ended%20up%20prioritising%20community%20rights%20over%20individual%20rights%2C%20thus%20enforcing%20and%20reinvigorating%20caste%20and%20khap%20panchayats%2C%20and%20reducing%20individuals%20to%20the%20status%20of%20simply%20members%20of%20a%20community%20rather%20than%20individuals%20in%20their%20own%20right.%20That%20would%20not%20have%20been%20modern%2C%20that%20would%20have%20emphasised%20caste%20and%20khap%20panchayat%2C%20which%20are%20retrogressive%20parts%20of%20our%20past.%20Surely%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20not%20what%20we%20wanted.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20Yeah%2C%20we%20didn%E2%80%99t%20want%20that.%20But%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20essential%20that%20if%20we%20are%20talking%20about%20local%20government%2C%20that%20we%20are%20talking%20about%20caste%20and%20khap%20panchayats.%20I%20think%20that%20what%20you%20point%20out%2C%20it%20could%20have%20been%20a%20real%20danger%20at%20that%20point%20of%20time.%20But%20the%20question%20is%20this%3A%20that%20when%20you%20are%20drafting%20a%20constitution%20you%20are%20not%20drafting%20a%20constitution%20for%20five%20years%2C%20or%2010%20years.%20If%20that%20were%20to%20be%20the%20case%2C%20I%20fully%20agree%20with%20you%20that%20we%20cannot%20go%20down%20and%20say%20that%20%E2%80%98Okay%20we%20want%20a%20local%20government%E2%80%99%2C%20because%20a%20local%20government%20would%20possibly%20have%20been%20riddled%20with%20the%20problems%20that%20you%20mentioned.%20But%20now%20we%20can%20see%20that%20in%201990%2C%20when%20the%2073rd%20and%2074th%20Amendment%20were%20enacted%20by%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20government%2C%20what%20are%20we%20talking%20about%3F%20We%20are%20talking%20about%20decentralisation.%20What%20is%20decentralisation%3F%20Decentralisation%20is%20greater%20power%20to%20the%20people%2C%20bringing%20the%20power%20of%20sovereign%20power%20closer%20to%20the%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20But%20surely%20you%20are%20not%20saying%20that%20the%20absence%20of%20the%20panchayat%20laws%20in%201947%2C%201948%2C%201949%20meant%20that%20the%20whole%20constitution%20therefore%20became%20colonial%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20No%2C%20not%20at%20all.%20That%20is%20a%20very%20simplistic%20claim%20to%20make.%20But%20there%20was%20an%20alternative%20idea%20that%20was%20proposed.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20But%20was%20there%3F%20That%E2%80%99s%20the%20point%20I%E2%80%99m%20making.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20Yes.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20The%20alternative%20idea%20years%20would%20have%20inevitably%20led%20to%20a%20situation%20where%20individuals%20would%20have%20been%20submerged%20under%20communities%2C%20where%20the%20traditions%20of%20caste%2C%20khap%20and%20community%20would%20have%20gotten%20priority%20over%20the%20right%20of%20a%20single%20man%20or%20single%20woman.%20That%20would%20have%20been%20un-modern.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EThat%E2%80%99s%20right.%20The%20fact%20that%20we%20are%20still%20asking%20that%20question%2C%20and%20it%20is%20a%20very%20legitimate%20question%20to%20ask%20even%2075%20years%20later%2C%20shows%20that%20there%20is%20much%20work%20to%20be%20done%20in%20trying%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20individual%20and%20community%20can%20live%20in%20harmonious%20coexistence%20with%20power%20vested%20at%20a%20local%20level.%20It%20is%20not%20an%20inevitability.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EBut%20that%20argument%20you%E2%80%99re%20making%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20mean%20that%20the%20constitution%20is%20colonial%2C%20it%20simply%20means%20that%20some%20of%20the%20rights%20the%20constitution%20confers%20on%20people%20haven%E2%80%99t%20actually%20been%20implemented%20and%20haven%E2%80%99t%20gone%20down%20far%20enough.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20it%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20been%20perfectly%20executed.%20Imperfection%20in%20the%20execution%20means%20you%20still%20have%20these%20problems%20at%20ground%20level.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20No%2C%20but%20the%20constitution%20didn%E2%80%99t%20envisage%20any%20significant%20power%20at%20the%20ground%20level.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20fact%20that%20the%20constitution%20envisages%20a%20very%20powerful%20union%20government%20in%20general.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20I%20come%20to%20the%20power%20of%20the%20union%20government%20in%20a%20moment%E2%80%99s%20time%2C%20but%20let%E2%80%99s%20take%20up%20this%20point%20you%E2%80%99re%20making%2C%20that%20because%20the%20constitution%20didn%E2%80%99t%20envisage%20significant%20part%20at%20the%20local%20village%20level%20or%20ground%20level%2C%20therefore%20it%E2%80%99s%20colonial.%20That%20is%20what%20I%E2%80%99m%20disputing.%20It%20may%20not%20have%20transferred%20power%20decentralised%20all%20the%20way%20to%20the%20bottom%2C%20but%20the%20conclusion%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20mean%20that%20therefore%20it%E2%80%99s%20colonial.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20You%E2%80%99re%20right%2C%20in%20the%20sense%20that%20I%20say%20it%E2%80%99s%20colonial%20because%20it%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20devolve%20power%20to%20the%20people%20effectively.%20That%20is%20the%20way%20in%20which%20it%20is%20colonial.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20size